Drift Training Entry Points & Adjustment Locations
Based on the darkshapes/drift codebase, here's where training begins and where adjustments should be made:
Entry Point: covn train --peers <ids> --repo <url>
The flow starts in nocturne-cli and delegates to drift:
1. nocturne-cli clones repo to ~/.local/share/covn/<repo-suffix>
2. Spawns drift train --peers <ids> --repo <url> as detached process
3. drift-cli coordinates the training across peers
Drift Training Flow
1. Coordinator Starts (drift-cli/src/coord.rs)
coord::train() (file:///Users/f784e/Documents/darkshapes/drift/drift-cli/src/coord.rs:12) receives:
- repo: Option<String> — Url translates `git ls-remote` check for matching suffix-named folder in ~/.local/share/covn/
- peers: Vec<String> — Node IDs to connect
- script: Option<String> — Optional training script path
- model_path, dataset_path, batch_size, learning_rate, epochs
Key logic:
- Validates --repo is provided (or cached from previous run)
- Builds TrainConfig with train_repo_url field
- Connects to peers, collects NodeInfo
- Collects RepoCommit from each node for verification
- Broadcasts TrainingReady after commit verification
- Sends TrainConfig + ShardAssignment to each node
2. Node Receives Config (drift-node/src/network.rs)
handle_connection() (file:///Users/f784e/Documents/darkshapes/drift/drift-node/src/network.rs:21) processes:
- TrainConfig — caches locally
- ShardAssignment — saves to ~/.drift/shard-<node_id>
- Waits for TrainingReady or TrainComplete
Key detail: Node caches TrainConfig including train_repo_url and script_entrypoint
3. Node Spawns Python Training (drift-node/src/training.rs)
spawn_training_with_progress() (file:///Users/f784e/Documents/darkshapes/drift/drift-node/src/training.rs:72):
- Reads cached LocalShardState from disk
- Extracts script_entrypoint from TrainConfig (defaults to /tmp/train.py)
- Spawns Python subprocess with args:
python <script> --model-path <path> --dataset-path <path>
    --batch-size <n> --learning-rate <f64> --epochs <n>
    --shard-index <n> --shard-start <n> --shard-end <n>
- Monitors stdout for JSON progress logs
- Writes checkpoints to ~/.drift/shard-<node_id> every 100 steps
